sentences: Glenn Morrison (born September 12, 1985) is a Canadian DJ and record producer from Toronto, Ontario.

In 2016, Morrison Recordings was closed down in order to allow Morrison the time and ability to create and run four new record labels -
Dying Light Records, Fall From Grace Records, Ambient Wave Records, and Wolfe Records.
In his early high school years, Morrison discovered Techno from a friend in his science class, and started collecting vinyl and becoming absorbed in underground DJ culture.
He then worked at Release Records for five years before starting his own record label Morrison Recordings.

His hit single ‘Goodbye’ has been Certified Double Platinum and went Number 1 for 11 weeks in a row on the Canadian Artists Billboard Chart, as well as going Number 1 in Russia, Ukraine and the Belarus Billboard Charts.
‘Goodbye’ was the 3rd highest grossing single for radio play in all genres for 2014 in Canada.
